sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M31518
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Refactored M13K07 from Hpa1 cut site to BamH1 cut site
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Refactored part of the M13K07 genome from the Hpa1 cut site to the BamH1 cut site. It is designed to not contain overlaps of DNA elements. Also, each gene has a particular function assigned to it. It is also designed so that future manipulations can be made easier.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sophie Wong
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Which restriction enzymes to include, which bases to mutate to eliminate overlaps of DNA elements.
